properties.description: Event home : https://www.facebook.com/asarkia.info/videos/2064528010514030/ Abkhaz youth joined “Fridays for Future» on March 15 It is the first time that Abkhazia supported such s global environment campaign initiated by Greta Thunberg from Sweden. Unlike other countries, Abkhazia held no meetings, and a campaign for the greening of Sukhum, the capital of Abkhazia. Thus, the activists planted 50 trees on Sukhum embankment. Numbers of young Abkhazian shoolchildren joined their worldwide counterparts. “Let’s safe our planet”, We don’t have other planet”, “12 years left”, such inscriptions could be seen on their banners. Abkhazian schoolchildren of all ages came to plant trees and help "breathe the planet". In their opinion, such actions can really help to reduce the global temperature on earth. "We learned - they commented - that on March 15, the world held a climate action and we also decided to do something for the planet." “About a million schoolchildren from 125 countries took part in the protests”, - Greta wrote on her Twitter. From Nauru and New Delhi to Munich and Mexico City, students walked out of school and took to the streets to express their position on environmental changes on our planet. “It will be too late for my generation", "Stop denying the fact that our Earth is dying", "Think about the future of the world", "Earth is the only place where you live", "more bikes — less cars", "Protect nature, and it will protect you", "Change politicians, not the climate" — such inscriptions were seen on the banners of protesters in different countries of the world.

The students explained how this protest’s objective is that of combatting the dangers that are being provoked by climate change.
